29:19.132 --> 29:21.217
-A microbrew.
-Yeah.

29:21.301 --> 29:23.178
-No.
-Right on, man.

29:23.928 --> 29:24.804
Bro!

29:25.263 --> 29:26.389
Oh, my God.

29:26.473 --> 29:29.058
Oh... What the hell? God!

29:29.768 --> 29:30.685
Excuse me.

29:31.186 --> 29:32.687
-Hey!
-I gotta go.

29:35.440 --> 29:36.733
-[clears throat]
-[beeps]

29:37.317 --> 29:38.151
Hello?

29:38.234 --> 29:40.153
Mom, I need your help.

29:40.236 --> 29:42.697
Rob, where are you?
Do you know what time it is?

29:42.781 --> 29:46.326
Mom, I'm freaking out. I'm butt-ass naked.
I'm 20 blocks from the hotel,

29:46.409 --> 29:49.245
and I keep repeating the same hour
over and over again.

29:49.329 --> 29:50.205
<i>What?</i>

29:50.288 --> 29:52.332
You naked... in public?

29:52.415 --> 29:55.794
Yes! This is the worst day of my life,
and I can't get it to end.

29:55.877 --> 29:57.712
Calm down, baby.

29:57.796 --> 29:59.756
Now, you ain't got no clothes on?

29:59.839 --> 30:01.341
I'm wearing a shopping bag.

30:01.424 --> 30:04.093
Can you find some other trash
that you can make a shirt out of?

30:04.177 --> 30:06.846
No, Mom,
all my stuff is back at the hotel.

30:06.930 --> 30:10.308
-Well, go on back to the hotel then!
-I told you, I don't have time.

30:10.391 --> 30:12.644
I have one hour,
and every time the church bells ring,

30:12.727 --> 30:14.270
I get sent back to the...

30:15.355 --> 30:17.190
Mom, put the pastor on.

30:17.857 --> 30:19.984
All right, good talk.

30:20.735 --> 30:22.070
Father Butterfield!

30:22.654 --> 30:23.822
Psst. Phone!

30:27.283 --> 30:29.994
-This is Father Butterfield.
-Yes, this is Rob, the groom.

30:30.078 --> 30:32.247
Listen, I was wondering
if it's at all possible,

30:32.330 --> 30:36.626
can you, like, not ring the church bells
for like a hour, an hour and a half?

30:36.709 --> 30:39.337
Because I think the church bells
are sending me back in time.

30:39.420 --> 30:41.923
Son, in our 208-year history,

30:42.006 --> 30:44.050
we've never once missed the bells
or a wedding.

30:44.133 --> 30:47.095
[scoffs] You mean to tell me
you never missed one wedding?

30:47.220 --> 30:48.596
Like, not even for the plague?

30:48.680 --> 30:49.514
Mnh-mnh.

30:49.597 --> 30:52.141
-How can you account for that?
-Faith.

30:52.934 --> 30:55.562
Or you are sending me back in time.

30:55.645 --> 30:57.981
Well, not you, but, like... God.

30:58.064 --> 31:00.441
-[church bells ringing]
-He's giving me a second chance.

31:00.525 --> 31:02.861
We're booked till August.
If you're thinking about rescheduling...

31:02.944 --> 31:06.114
Well, apparently I don't have to.
This wedding is happening!

31:06.197 --> 31:07.532
So does that mean you're coming?

31:08.157 --> 31:10.410
Maybe not to this one, but I'm coming.

31:12.495 --> 31:13.788
Remember me?

31:14.497 --> 31:15.415
[grunts]

31:15.498 --> 31:19.544
-[pounding]
-<i>♪ Bye-bye, love ♪</i>

31:19.627 --> 31:23.298
<i>♪ Bye-bye, happiness ♪</i>

31:23.798 --> 31:26.634
-Okay.
-<i>♪ Hello, loneliness ♪</i>

31:29.804 --> 31:31.389
-[exhales]
-[elevator bell dings]

31:33.057 --> 31:34.893
[all] Oh!

31:34.976 --> 31:35.852
[men grunting]

31:35.935 --> 31:39.314
Hey, I just wanna say I'm sorry
about earlier. No hard feelings?

31:41.941 --> 31:43.151
You don't even know, huh?

31:46.237 --> 31:47.447
[camera shutter clicks]

31:47.947 --> 31:50.950
All right, people, move out of my way.
Brother gotta go.

32:05.048 --> 32:08.009
Hey, nerds, you guys got a skateboard,
some Heelys or something?

32:08.092 --> 32:09.886
Hey, soccer mom. Ma'am, please.
No? Thank you.

32:09.969 --> 32:12.555
Hey, sister, you got a bus pass, anything?
God damn.

32:12.639 --> 32:15.183
Hi. Hi, ma'am, can you please help me?

32:18.269 --> 32:19.604
What the hell?

32:27.987 --> 32:31.032
Where's the keys? Oh, keys?

32:31.115 --> 32:33.326
Keys? Where do you put keys on a bike?

32:33.409 --> 32:34.702
You want to buy it a drink?

32:36.287 --> 32:37.747
Hey... um...

32:38.873 --> 32:39.958
Drill?

32:40.625 --> 32:43.086
I was just... checking out your bike.

32:43.169 --> 32:44.921
I thought about getting a bike myself,

32:45.004 --> 32:47.882
but you know,
my girl said it's too dangerous.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.968
You know how old ladies are, right?

32:50.051 --> 32:53.137
-Who he talking about?
-You calling my lady old, man?

32:53.221 --> 32:55.682
No, not that you old.
You got a young face.

32:56.140 --> 32:58.601
This dude knows what I mean. My man. Bra.

32:59.394 --> 33:01.396
Oh, oh, oh!

33:01.479 --> 33:03.648
-Oh, boy.
-Did he just knock down my bike?

33:03.731 --> 33:06.192
-He knocked down the bike.
-No! It jumped. I didn't...

33:06.275 --> 33:08.695
-No, I didn't do it.
-You didn't do it? You got some money?

33:09.195 --> 33:10.738
Just this.

33:10.822 --> 33:11.948
Eat it.

33:12.740 --> 33:14.158
That's kind of unsanitary.

33:14.242 --> 33:15.576
-I ain't eating--
-Eat it!

33:24.794 --> 33:27.922
I think I got a half a dollar stuck
in my larynx.

33:28.006 --> 33:29.841
[choking]

33:30.717 --> 33:32.593
[coughs and swallows]

33:32.677 --> 33:33.761
Thank you.

33:33.845 --> 33:36.139
You look like you got lost
on your way to the shower.

33:36.222 --> 33:37.390
Um...

33:38.016 --> 33:41.477
-I was just on my way to my wedding.
-[woman] He ain't gonna make it.

33:41.561 --> 33:43.604
He ain't gonna make it, huh?
Well, you need a ride?

33:44.147 --> 33:45.815
Are you serious? You would...

33:45.898 --> 33:48.317
-You would do that for me?
-Yeah, of course.

33:48.401 --> 33:49.527
You guys!

33:50.111 --> 33:52.530
Yeah, I would love a ride. Thank you.

33:52.613 --> 33:54.741
-Call an ambulance.
-An ambulance?

33:54.824 --> 33:56.659
[screams]

33:56.743 --> 34:00.997
Okay, guys, please. Please! Please!
I got my ass kicked twice already. Twice.

34:01.080 --> 34:03.166
It's his wedding day!
I think he need a shave!

34:03.249 --> 34:04.792
I just want this to be over.

34:04.876 --> 34:07.336
I spent the last six months talking
about locations.

34:07.420 --> 34:09.338
By the way,
you have a very beautiful city.

34:09.422 --> 34:11.591
-[screams]
-Hold him down like that, man!

34:11.674 --> 34:13.760
She even made me take dance lessons!

34:15.053 --> 34:17.263
Hey, let him up. I wanna see this.
Let him up!

34:21.016 --> 34:22.226
Show me.

34:22.351 --> 34:24.145
Sh-- Sh-- Show you what?

34:24.228 --> 34:25.438
Our dance routine?

34:25.521 --> 34:27.440
Well, I didn't really learn it.

34:27.523 --> 34:29.734
I didn't think
it was terribly important at the time.

34:29.817 --> 34:30.650
-[woman] Oh, no.
-What?

34:30.735 --> 34:31.694
[Rob] Yeah.

34:31.777 --> 34:34.572
-That's the centerpiece of the reception.
-All right. All right.

34:34.655 --> 34:37.324
Come on, back up. Give him room now.
Give him room. Let him breathe.

34:37.408 --> 34:38.784
Can I use your man right there?

34:39.284 --> 34:42.205
I come up and-- You first come up and--

34:42.288 --> 34:43.998
<i>♪ Everybody dance now ♪</i>

34:44.956 --> 34:46.626
-Slap it hard.
-[all] Oh!

34:46.708 --> 34:48.168
Come here and you grab like this.

34:48.252 --> 34:51.172
You my bitch. Okay, I lead, you follow.

34:51.630 --> 34:54.759
And then, I come around like this here,
and I dip you.

34:54.842 --> 34:56.761
But your big ass is too big to dip.

34:56.844 --> 34:59.889
Bring you back up, and then I start
slow grinding 'cause it's our way.

34:59.972 --> 35:02.391
-Come on, man!
-Come on! Just a slow grind!

35:02.475 --> 35:05.311
And that leads you into the Running Man
like... Oh, oh, oh, oh!

35:05.394 --> 35:06.938
And slide and pose.

35:09.941 --> 35:12.944
And then I pull myself back up,
and then start pop-locking.

35:13.027 --> 35:15.113
Bam! Bam! [exclaims]

35:15.196 --> 35:18.616
Listen to my crowd when I pop like...
'cause it's so hard.

35:18.699 --> 35:20.993
They start whopping
'cause black girls love to whop.

35:21.077 --> 35:22.954
-Hey! Hey!
-Hey.

35:23.037 --> 35:26.499
Then you show them your flexibility.
You be like... oh! Oh!

35:26.582 --> 35:28.876
Oh! Oh!

35:28.960 --> 35:30.878
After that, we all get in a circle like...

35:32.964 --> 35:34.090
Work that body.

35:34.173 --> 35:36.217
[Rob grunting]

35:36.801 --> 35:37.802
Break it down.

35:37.885 --> 35:39.804
[vocalizing]

35:43.015 --> 35:44.851
Hey, cut that out, man!

35:44.934 --> 35:46.894
You got me up here
doing a Bobby Brown dance.

35:46.978 --> 35:48.187
-[woman] You don't.
-I don't dance!

35:48.271 --> 35:49.188
No, you don't!

35:49.272 --> 35:52.191
Okay, so, I may have missed
a few classes or two.

35:52.650 --> 35:55.069
What you think, baby?
You think his old lady gonna like that?

35:55.153 --> 35:57.822
I think she gonna kick his ass,
messing up that first dance.

35:57.905 --> 35:59.407
It's disrespectful.

35:59.991 --> 36:01.075
I'd like to see that.

36:02.243 --> 36:03.953
-Let's ride!
-Really?

36:04.036 --> 36:07.290
-Get your ass on the bike!
-Hey, but I ain't riding bitch!

36:07.415 --> 36:10.209
-[man] Who you calling "bitch"?
-Unless you want me to. [chuckles]

36:11.169 --> 36:12.003
Let's go!

36:25.183 --> 36:27.268
We got this. We got this.

36:29.478 --> 36:30.771
We got it, baby!

36:31.522 --> 36:32.690
[screams]

36:32.773 --> 36:35.193
[grunts] No!

36:35.276 --> 36:37.069
[screams, grunts]

36:37.153 --> 36:38.946
[siren wailing]

36:39.030 --> 36:40.156
[tires screeching]

36:44.952 --> 36:46.245
[screams]

36:46.329 --> 36:48.748
-Okay.
-What happened?

36:48.831 --> 36:51.375
-You hit a barricade at 40 miles an hour.
-Where am I?

36:51.959 --> 36:54.295
-All right, what's your name?
-It's Rob. Rob Anderson.

36:54.378 --> 36:56.339
And, Rob, can you tell me what day it is?

36:56.422 --> 36:58.132
It's my wedding day. It's my wedding day.

36:58.216 --> 37:01.052
I gotta get ready. I'm getting married
right there at that church!

37:01.177 --> 37:02.511
-You're suffering from a concussion.
-No!

37:02.595 --> 37:04.889
The only thing you're marrying today
is a catheter.

37:04.972 --> 37:08.100
-No. I gotta get to my wedding!
-I got a better idea.

37:08.184 --> 37:11.020
You take five more CCs of Ativan.

37:11.103 --> 37:14.023
-No. No. No! [screams]
-Rob!

37:15.191 --> 37:16.776
[winces]

37:16.859 --> 37:19.362
[panting]

37:22.782 --> 37:24.659
I want you to keep reaching out
to shareholders.

37:24.742 --> 37:26.911
Give them what they want,
but do it quietly.

37:26.994 --> 37:29.872
I don't want this getting leaked
before we announce next week.

37:29.956 --> 37:30.998
All right?

37:33.709 --> 37:35.336
[grunting]

37:36.337 --> 37:37.922
Anderson, what happened? Are you drunk?

37:38.673 --> 37:40.007
I'm not drunk.

37:41.342 --> 37:42.510
I'm on drugs.

37:48.391 --> 37:50.017
-Ugh.
-[heaves]

37:51.560 --> 37:53.521
Oh, God. Did you just puke coins?

37:56.983 --> 38:00.611
Would you look at that? A bicentennial.

38:00.695 --> 38:03.906
You know, these are worth a lot of money.
You keep that for me.

38:07.034 --> 38:10.204
I don't get it.
In what world did she pick you over me?

38:10.288 --> 38:11.831
I made a hundred mill last year.

38:11.914 --> 38:13.582
You made a hundred mill?

38:13.666 --> 38:15.084
I should fucking rob you.

38:15.167 --> 38:17.712
Why are you dressed
like some Vegas housewife,

38:17.795 --> 38:19.422
with your gross, busted up arm?

38:19.505 --> 38:20.756
Seriously, is that thing real?

38:20.840 --> 38:22.383
What are you talking about? This...

38:22.466 --> 38:25.219
[gasping]

38:25.303 --> 38:27.930
-That's pretty broken.
-Yeah, it looks like a Krazy Straw.

38:28.014 --> 38:30.016
It kind of does. Look at...

38:31.142 --> 38:32.310
It's not really a straw.

38:32.393 --> 38:34.437
[laughs]

38:34.520 --> 38:35.688
Watch this.

38:35.771 --> 38:38.858
-Oh, no! No!
-[screams]

38:38.941 --> 38:41.610
[laughs] I can't feel a thing!

38:42.194 --> 38:45.031
You know, that girl has been dreaming
about this day her entire life,

38:45.114 --> 38:46.198
and this is...

38:47.074 --> 38:48.909
[sighs] what you're bringing to the table?

38:54.040 --> 38:55.166
[sobs]

38:55.916 --> 38:57.501
You're so right.

38:58.210 --> 39:01.714
She's not gonna marry me
looking like this.

39:01.797 --> 39:03.883
I just want a hug.

39:03.966 --> 39:06.719
Look, showing up is half the battle.
The other half is pants.

39:06.802 --> 39:09.472
Go home and put some pants on,
for God's sakes. Go! [snaps fingers]

39:09.555 --> 39:10.556
Come on.

39:14.602 --> 39:15.728
Whoa!

39:17.021 --> 39:19.315
I-- I see what's going on here.

39:19.899 --> 39:24.820
You want me to waltz on out of here
so that I can miss my wedding, huh?

39:24.904 --> 39:28.657
Oh, yeah, because your little plot...

39:28.741 --> 39:31.702
to leave me trapped inside the elevator...

39:32.453 --> 39:33.662
blew up in your...

39:35.998 --> 39:38.959
Whoo, I am high.

39:40.086 --> 39:40.920
...face.

39:41.003 --> 39:42.880
First of all,
that sounds like a terrible plan,

39:42.963 --> 39:45.049
and second,
I have three women who can confirm

39:45.132 --> 39:46.884
I was in my hotel room
with them all night.

39:46.967 --> 39:48.636
Third, if I wanted to ruin your wedding,

39:48.719 --> 39:50.304
I'd just let you walk in there right now.

39:50.388 --> 39:51.263
[moaning]

39:51.347 --> 39:54.725
Which I just realized
would be absolutely perfect.

39:55.393 --> 39:57.603
-Come on, let's go get you married.
-I don't...

39:57.686 --> 39:59.397
-Here we go.
-I don't wanna get married.

39:59.480 --> 40:00.689
Just gonna walk right in.

40:00.773 --> 40:03.275
-[church bells ringing]
-Wait, hold on! It's the wedding bells!

40:03.359 --> 40:04.902
Ah, thank God!

40:05.528 --> 40:08.781
-[pounding]
<i>-♪ Bye-bye, love ♪</i>

40:08.864 --> 40:11.951
<i>-♪ Bye-bye, happiness ♪</i>
-I need pants.

40:12.034 --> 40:13.744
[elevator bell dings]

40:25.423 --> 40:27.466
-Hey! Call an ambulance!
-Why?

40:28.259 --> 40:29.135
[grunts]

40:29.802 --> 40:30.803
Damn.

40:30.886 --> 40:31.762
Hey!

40:32.346 --> 40:33.556
[grunts]

40:34.140 --> 40:36.475
Ah! [sighs]

40:42.565 --> 40:45.818
-[exhales]
-Yes! Whoo! My man's in the house!

40:45.901 --> 40:49.822
-Come on, everybody, give it up!
-[cheering]

40:49.905 --> 40:52.908
[man shouting] Rob! Rob!

41:00.416 --> 41:01.792
[whispers] Don't ask, just...

41:03.711 --> 41:04.795
These are tight.

41:04.879 --> 41:06.755
-[Ben] What you got on?
-I'm adjusting this.

41:06.839 --> 41:09.383
It goes over to the side. That's weird.

41:10.843 --> 41:13.304
["Bridal Chorus" playing]

41:29.987 --> 41:32.698
-Aw, come on, brother.
-No, just pull it back, pull it down.

41:32.781 --> 41:35.534
-I can't.
-Pull it down. Okay, stop that hurts.

41:36.577 --> 41:38.037
Okay. Just relax.

41:38.120 --> 41:40.414
Yeah, that ain't got room for that. Okay.

41:41.874 --> 41:43.083
I'll be right back.

41:43.918 --> 41:44.752
Aw, baby...

41:47.087 --> 41:49.131
Baby, I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

41:49.215 --> 41:51.175
I just grabbed
the first thing I could find.

41:51.258 --> 41:54.094
It just needs to be taken out in the back,
just a little bit.

41:54.637 --> 41:56.764
-Oh, I'm gonna take it out in the back.
-[stammers]

41:56.847 --> 41:58.224
[crowd gasps]

41:58.307 --> 41:59.975
Baby, I think we're going to the cleaners.

42:00.601 --> 42:02.770
-Daddy, no!
-[church bells ringing]

42:02.853 --> 42:03.771
[grunts]

42:10.277 --> 42:11.278
[screams]

42:12.696 --> 42:15.533
If you're gonna show up in that,
then don't show up at all.

42:15.616 --> 42:18.869
[screams, grunts]

42:18.953 --> 42:22.373
If you're gonna show up in that,
then don't show up at all.

42:24.708 --> 42:26.293
I've tried everything:

42:26.377 --> 42:30.214
smart corduroy, seersucker,
a Nehru jacket.

42:30.297 --> 42:33.259
-What do you want from me?
-I want you to be somebody else.

42:33.842 --> 42:35.344
Megan is the only daughter I have.

42:35.427 --> 42:38.055
I didn't raise her alone,
put her through medical school

42:38.138 --> 42:42.017
just to watch some lazy, thoughtless loser
come along and screw it up.

42:43.519 --> 42:44.687
Let's face it...

42:45.396 --> 42:48.274
you don't like me because I'm not
a fancy businessman like you or Cody.

42:55.447 --> 42:57.491
I don't dislike you for who you are, Rob.

42:57.575 --> 43:01.579
It's that you have no goals,
no ambition, no career.

43:02.454 --> 43:03.664
I'm a substitute teacher.

43:04.415 --> 43:08.002
Robert, marriage is not a part-time thing.

43:08.085 --> 43:10.838
I built a multinational company
from the ground up,

43:10.921 --> 43:13.507
and the toughest job I ever had
was being a husband.

43:14.091 --> 43:16.677
I'm talking long hours, overtime...

43:17.595 --> 43:19.305
and we didn't take summers off.

43:21.765 --> 43:26.145
When I gave this ring to Megan's mother,
I promised to give her everything I had.

43:26.228 --> 43:28.939
That I'd never stop proving myself to her,

43:29.023 --> 43:31.317
and that I'd never, ever stop loving her.

43:32.234 --> 43:34.361
This ring symbolizes that promise.

43:35.279 --> 43:36.530
It's very simple, son.

43:37.031 --> 43:38.616
You gotta put in the work.

43:39.783 --> 43:40.868
You're just not that guy.

43:41.994 --> 43:43.954
I wish my daughter would see that.

43:49.710 --> 43:53.380
You know, you're really protective
of your daughter.

43:53.464 --> 43:56.258
-There's nothing I wouldn't do for her.
-Nothing?

43:56.342 --> 43:57.885
Not even kidnapping?

43:57.968 --> 43:59.136
What?

44:00.721 --> 44:01.889
Someone...

44:02.514 --> 44:05.309
